# MODULAR: .gitignore for proxy/. The proxy is a Node service;
# any compiled output, dev-time caches, or local-only data
# belong here rather than at the repo root (which is shared
# with the web client + scripts + docs).
#
# ORGANIZED: the repo-root .gitignore is the single source
# of truth for the project's ignore list. This file is
# a complement for files that only make sense inside
# proxy/ — e.g. node --test's per-file db files, or
# generated API clients (none today; the file is forward-
# looking).

*.js.map
*.d.ts
node_modules/
coverage/
.cache/
